                                                                                                                                     NATION BRIEFS
               
	 Mumbai, Jan. 6 (PTI): Bhadant Sanghraj Thairo, the priest of Sandesh Buddh Vihar at Deonar here, was found dead at his home behind the shrine today, triggering arson in the area. 
     
	Police said it seemed to be a suicide. But a monk registered a murder complaint, said DCP Niket Kaushik. 
     
	He said residents alleged a builder eyeing the nearby area could be behind it. Sporadic incidents of arson, stone-pelting and shops being forcibly shut were reported. 
         
	New Delhi (PTI): About 30 flights were delayed by fog on Sunday and one was diverted to Jaipur despite low visibility procedures being implemented at IGI airport. 
         
	New Delhi (PTI): A fire killed seven persons and gutted around 300 shanties near north Delhis Lahori gate on Sunday. 
                                                            
